## 7. Version drift — bump in 4 places

**Problem:** The app version is spread across independent files. Forgetting any one causes cache-bust mismatches or stale health markers.

**All places to bump:**
1. `public/app.js` — `const APP_VERSION = 'x.y.z'`
2. `public/index.html` — `?v=x.y.z` on CSS/JS `<link>` and `<script>` tags
3. `server.js` — `APP_VERSION` is read from `package.json` dynamically (auto), but check the health endpoint
4. `package.json` — the source of truth for `APP_VERSION`

**Heads-up:** `public/app.js` has a hardcoded `APP_VERSION` string. When releasing, update all non-dynamic references.

